result.name: Shek Wai Kok Estate

reviews.text: Wow what a great place I have been ever!

Quiet place; many food stores and restaurants, a residential area; during lunch time, many many students will be there around, since few secondary schools there are setting the same time as lunch break; not a good place for tourists; very very local, the waiters/waitresses are not young, they normally don’t know what are you talking about while you speak English; just use your finger to poke the menu if it has pictures (normally don’t have), or you can point other customer’s dish/food for ordering things (not really impolite since they know you are tourist). If you wanna experience the real hk life, you are welcome to go, and remember to bring cash, not many of them have credit card reader; good luck and get lost
Poor people living place

Nice & peaceful public housing village with above standard rubbish disposable facilities for older style public housing that had been built for a couple of decades. The village residents seem to be friendly & the security system/facility in place provides a sense of security for both visitors & residents.
Great place to live but you gotta buy it
